rn), showing their mutual correspondences and emphasizing the relationship between the Slavic pre-Christian religion and its Indo-European roots.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / Paganism & Neo-Paganism.2bisacsh  aBaltic peoples.  aSlavic peoples.  aearly Middle Ages.  afolklore.  apagan religions.1 aSantos Marinas, Enrique, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802701173?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802701173zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802701173/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131928-5 EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA